title: Readout of the Vice President's Call with President Erdogan of Turkey | whitehouse.gov
content:
The White House
Office of the Vice President


For Immediate Release
October 03, 2014

 



Readout of the Vice President's Call with President Erdogan of Turkey




Vice President Joe Biden spoke today with Turkish President Recep Tayyip Erdogan to follow up on their meeting in New York on September 25. The two leaders discussed ways the United States and Turkey can work together to degrade and destroy the Islamic State of Iraq and Levant (ISIL) and restore security and stability to the region.Â
